nslation framed by an introduction that contextualizes the text, and accompanied by annotations, maps, and illustrations, The Deeds of Philip Augustus makes one of the most important documents of twelfth-century France available to wide new readership.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 4aBiography & Autobiography. 4aFrance. 4aMedieval & Renaissance Studies. 7aHISTORY / Medieval.2bisacsh  agesta philippi augusti, third crusade, albigensian crusade, king phillip II of France, king phillip augustus expulsion of the jews.1 aField, Larry F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aField, Sean L., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGaposchkin, M. Cecilia, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHyams, Paul R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311075182608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2022 Englishz978311099296008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2022z9783110992939oZDB-23-DEG40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150176317540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501763175423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501763175/original  a978-3-11-075182-6  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-099296-0  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099389-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishb2022  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  a